My Review: I was very underwhelmed with this book. Over half of it is dedicated to a single day, and while the consequences of that day are felt in the remainder, there isn’t much time to address them. Beyond that, while the writing is interesting and varied, the story really isn’t. I wasn’t aware of the subject of the book before reading it and probably wouldn’t have read it had I known.
